A2-205.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2-206.name: Palkia ex

attack.effect: Discard 3 {W} Energy from this Pokémon. This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

A2-206.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2-003.name: Bellossom
A2-003.text:
Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals
rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

A2-010.name: Turtwig
A2-010.text:
It uses its whole body to photosynthesize when
exposed to sunlight. Its shell is made from
hardened soil.

A2-011.name: Grotle
A2-011.text:
It lives along water in forests. In the daytime,
it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

A2-012.name: Torterra

attack.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Frenzy Plant.

A2-012.text:
Ancient people imagined that beneath the
ground dwelt a gigantic Torterra.

A2-013.name: Kricketot
A2-013.text:
Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff
antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.

A2-014.name: Kricketune

attack.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

A2-014.text:
By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its
belly, it produces a captivating sound.

A2-016.name: Wormadam

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

A2-016.text:
Its appearance changes depending on where it
evolved. The materials on hand become a part of
its body.

A2-019.name: Carnivine

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

A2-019.text:
It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then
chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

A2-023.name: Magmar

attack.effect: Take a {R} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

A2-023.text:
Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it
regrets this habit once it realizes that it has
burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

A2-024.name: Magmortar

attack.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

A2-024.text:
When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning
in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to
over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

A2-026.name: Magcargo

attack.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

A2-026.text:
Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames
that circulate throughout its body.

A2-027.name: Chimchar
A2-027.text:
Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly.
Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

A2-028.name: Monferno
A2-028.text:
It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its
tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

A2-029.name: Infernape ex

attack.effect: Discard all {R} Energy from this Pokémon.

A2-029.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2-034.name: Regice

ability.effect: Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent’s Pokémon done to this Pokémon.

A2-034.text:
With cold air that can reach temperatures as low
as −328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly
freezes any creature that approaches it.

A2-035.name: Piplup

attack.effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

A2-035.text:
It doesn’t like to be taken care of. It’s difficult to
bond with since it won’t listen to its Trainer.

A2-036.name: Prinplup
A2-036.text:
It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every
one of them believes it is the most important.

A2-037.name: Empoleon

attack.effect: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

A2-037.text:
It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its
wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

A2-038.name: Buizel
A2-038.text:
It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself
through water. The tails also slice clinging
seaweed.

A2-040.name: Shellos
A2-040.text:
It used to have a shell on its back long ago.
This species is closely related to Pokémon
like Shellder.

A2-041.name: Gastrodon

attack.effect: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

A2-041.text:
They normally inhabit rocky seashores, but in
times of continuous rain, they can sometimes be
found in the mountains, far from the sea.

A2-046.name: Glaceon

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

A2-046.text:
It can control its body temperature at will.
This enables it to freeze the moisture in the
atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.

A2-049.name: Palkia ex

attack.effect: Discard 3 {W} Energy from this Pokémon. This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

A2-049.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2-050.name: Manaphy

attack.effect: Choose 2 of your Benched Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, take a {W} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to that Pokémon.

A2-050.text:
It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond
with any kind of Pokémon.

A2-054.name: Voltorb

attack.effect: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

A2-054.text:
It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden
jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

A2-062.name: Rotom

attack.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage.

A2-062.text:
Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds
of machines and take control in order to make
mischief.

A2-064.name: Togetic
A2-064.text:
They say that it will appear before kindhearted,
caring people and shower them with happiness.

A2-066.name: Misdreavus
A2-066.text:
This Pokémon startles people in the middle of
the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

A2-067.name: Mismagius ex

attack.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

A2-067.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2-075.name: Uxie

attack.effect: Take a {P} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to Mesprit or Azelf.

A2-075.text:
Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said
that it can wipe out the memory of those who see
its eyes.

A2-076.name: Mesprit

attack.effect: You can use this attack only if you have Uxie and Azelf on your Bench. Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

A2-076.text:
Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught
humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

A2-077.name: Azelf

attack.effect: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

A2-077.text:
Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the
bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

A2-078.name: Giratina

ability.effect: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

A2-078.text:
This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the
reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is
distorted and strange.

A2-079.name: Cresselia

attack.effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

A2-079.text:
Shiny particles are released from its wings like a
veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

A2-080.name: Rhyhorn
A2-080.text:
Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can
shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

A2-081.name: Rhydon
A2-081.text:
It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution.
It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

A2-082.name: Rhyperior

attack.effect: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck.

A2-082.text:
It can load up to three projectiles per arm into
the holes in its hands. What launches out of those
holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.

A2-087.name: Regirock

ability.effect: This Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

A2-087.text:
Every bit of Regirock’s body is made of stone.
As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks
rocks to itself to repair what’s been lost.

A2-093.name: Hippopotas
A2-093.text:
It shuts its nostrils tight, then travels through sand
as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.

A2-094.name: Hippowdon
A2-094.text:
It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth
agape as a display of its strength.

A2-098.name: Sneasel

attack.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

A2-098.text:
This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of
darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

A2-099.name: Weavile ex

attack.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 40 more damage.

A2-099.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2-100.name: Poochyena
A2-100.text:
A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its
chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

A2-104.name: Spiritomb

attack.effect: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon.

A2-104.text:
Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted
in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a
mysterious spell.

A2-106.name: Drapion

attack.effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

A2-106.text:
Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This
Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead,
going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

A2-111.name: Skarmory

attack.effect: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage.

A2-111.text:
People fashion swords from Skarmory’s shed
feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element
in heraldic designs.

A2-113.name: Shieldon
A2-113.text:
A mild-mannered, herbivorous Pokémon, it used
its face to dig up tree roots to eat. The skin on
its face was plenty tough.

A2-114.name: Bastiodon

ability.effect: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokémon takes −100 damage from that attack.

A2-114.text:
The bones of its face are huge and hard, so
they were mistaken for its spine until after this
Pokémon was successfully restored.

A2-115.name: Wormadam

attack.effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

A2-115.text:
Its appearance changes depending on where it
evolved. The materials on hand become a part of
its body.

A2-118.name: Probopass

attack.effect: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 more damage for each heads.

A2-118.text:
Although it can control its units known as
Mini-Noses, they sometimes get lost and don’t
come back.

A2-121.name: Gible
A2-121.text:
It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy
passes by, it leaps out and chomps them.
The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

A2-122.name: Gabite
A2-122.text:
In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales.
Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient
will make a weary body feel invigorated.

A2-123.name: Garchomp

A2b-001.text:
Often found in forests and grasslands.
It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches
on top of its head.

A2b-002.name: Kakuna

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

A2b-002.text:
Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only
harden its shell to protect itself when it is
in danger.

attack.effect: Discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

A2b-003.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2b-004.name: Pinsir

attack.effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

A2b-004.text:
These Pokémon judge one another based on
pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make
for more popularity with the opposite gender.

A2b-005.name: Sprigatito

attack.effect: Put 1 random {G} Pokémon from your deck into your hand.

A2b-005.text:
Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants.
This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep
it from drying out.

A2b-006.name: Floragato
A2b-006.text:
Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath
its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against
its opponents.

A2b-007.name: Meowscarada

attack.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 70 more damage.

A2b-007.text:
This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its
cape to camouflage the stem of its flower,
creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

A2b-008.name: Charmander
A2b-008.text:
It has a preference for hot things. When it rains,
steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

A2b-009.name: Charmeleon
A2b-009.text:
It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its
fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

A2b-010.name: Charizard ex

attack.effect: Take 3 {R} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

A2b-010.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2b-011.name: Magmar
A2b-011.text:
Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it
regrets this habit once it realizes that it has
burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

A2b-012.name: Magmortar

attack.effect: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

A2b-012.text:
When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning
in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to
over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

A2b-013.name: Paldean Tauros

attack.effect: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

A2b-013.text:
When heated by fire energy, its horns can get
hotter than 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. Those
gored by them will suffer both wounds and burns.

A2b-014.name: Tentacool
A2b-014.text:
Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer.
It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it
searches for prey.

A2b-015.name: Tentacruel
A2b-015.text:
When the red orbs on Tentacruel’s head glow
brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to
fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

A2b-016.name: Buizel
A2b-016.text:
It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above
water in order to watch for prey movement.

A2b-017.name: Floatzel

attack.effect: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

A2b-017.text:
With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people
on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

A2b-018.name: Wiglett

attack.effect: 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is chosen at random. Do 30 damage to it.

A2b-018.text:
This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza
just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in
the sand.

A2b-019.name: Wugtrio ex

attack.effect: 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is chosen at random 3 times. For each time a Pokémon was chosen, do 50 damage to it.

A2b-019.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2b-020.name: Dondozo

attack.effect: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

A2b-020.text:
This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting
food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

A2b-021.name: Tatsugiri

ability.effect: Your Active Dondozo has no Retreat Cost.

A2b-021.text:
This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the
mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies
on the outside.

A2b-022.name: Pikachu ex

attack.effect: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

A2b-022.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2b-023.name: Voltorb
A2b-023.text:
It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden
jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

A2b-024.name: Electrode

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

A2b-024.text:
The more energy it charges up, the faster
it gets. But this also makes it more likely
to explode.

A2b-025.name: Pachirisu

attack.effect: Take a {L} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched {L} Pokémon.

A2b-025.text:
It’s one of the kinds of Pokémon with electric
cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

A2b-026.name: Pawmi
A2b-026.text:
It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks.
These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi
rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.

A2b-027.name: Pawmo
A2b-027.text:
When its group is attacked, Pawmo is the first
to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a
fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.

A2b-028.name: Pawmot

ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

A2b-028.text:
This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once
it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies
with lightning-fast movements.

A2b-029.name: Abra
A2b-029.text:
This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it
sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the
powers that the Pokémon wields.

A2b-030.name: Kadabra
A2b-030.text:
Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it
sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

A2b-031.name: Alakazam

attack.effect: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any Energy attached.

A2b-031.text:
It has an incredibly high level of intelligence.
Some say that Alakazam remembers everything
that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

A2b-032.name: Mr. Mime

attack.effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

A2b-032.text:
The broadness of its hands may be no
coincidence—many scientists believe its palms
became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

A2b-033.name: Drifloon
A2b-033.text:
It is whispered that any child who mistakes
Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could
wind up missing.

A2b-034.name: Drifblim
A2b-034.text:
It can generate and release gas within its body.
That’s how it can control the altitude of its drift.

A2b-035.name: Giratina ex

attack.effect: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may take a Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

A2b-035.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2b-036.name: Gimmighoul

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

A2b-036.text:
This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest
about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force
out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

A2b-037.name: Machop
A2b-037.text:
Its whole body is composed of muscles.
Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can
hurl 100 grown-ups.

A2b-038.name: Machoke

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

A2b-038.text:
Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a
power-save belt to be able to regulate
its motions.

A2b-039.name: Machamp

attack.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra {F} Energy attached, this attack does 50 more damage.

A2b-039.text:
It quickly swings its four arms to rock its
opponents with ceaseless punches and chops
from all angles.

A2b-040.name: Hitmonlee
A2b-040.text:
This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of
balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

A2b-041.name: Hitmonchan
A2b-041.text:
Its punches slice the air. They are launched at
such high speed, even a slight graze could cause
a burn.

A2b-042.name: Riolu
A2b-042.text:
They communicate with one another using their
auras. They are able to run all through the night.

A2b-043.name: Lucario ex

attack.effect: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

A2b-043.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2b-044.name: Flamigo

attack.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

A2b-044.text:
This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck
into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does
not escape from its beak.

A2b-045.name: Ekans
A2b-045.text:
By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger
than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

A2b-046.name: Arbok

attack.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

A2b-046.text:
After stunning its opponents with the pattern
on its stomach, it quickly wraps them up in its
body and waits for them to stop moving.

A2b-047.name: Paldean Wooper

attack.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

A2b-047.text:
After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began
living on land. The Pokémon changed over time,
developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

A2b-048.name: Paldean Clodsire ex

attack.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 60 more damage.

A2b-048.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2b-049.name: Spiritomb

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

A2b-049.text:
Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted
in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a
mysterious spell.

A2b-050.name: Shroodle
A2b-050.text:
Though usually a mellow Pokémon, it will sink its
sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that
anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its ire.

A2b-051.name: Grafaiai

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

A2b-051.text:
The color of the poisonous saliva depends on
what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers
in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.

A2b-052.name: Tinkatink
A2b-052.text:
It swings its handmade hammer around to protect
itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon
that eat metal.

A2b-053.name: Tinkatuff

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

A2b-053.text:
This Pokémon will attack groups of Pawniard and
Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to
create a large and sturdy hammer.

A2b-054.name: Tinkaton ex

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

A2b-054.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2b-055.name: Varoom
A2b-055.text:
It is said that this Pokémon was born when an
unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited
an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

A2b-056.name: Revavroom

attack.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

A2b-056.text:
It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from
rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders—
now numbering eight—to generate energy.

A2b-057.name: Gholdengo

attack.effect: Flip a coin for each {M} Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

A2b-057.text:
Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins.
This Pokémon gets along well with others and is
quick to make friends with anybody.

A2b-058.name: Rattata
A2b-058.text:
Its incisors grow continuously throughout its life.
If its incisors get too long, this Pokémon
becomes unable to eat, and it starves to death.

A2b-059.name: Raticate
A2b-059.text:
People say that it fled from its enemies by
using its small webbed hind feet to swim
from island to island in Alola.

A2b-060.name: Jigglypuff
A2b-060.text:
It hugely inflates its stomach and sings a
mysterious melody. If you hear this melody,
you’ll become sleepy right away.

A2b-061.name: Wigglytuff

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Pokémon.

A2b-061.text:
It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it
angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a
body slam.

A2b-062.name: Lickitung
A2b-062.text:
If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and
you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in.
The itch won’t go away, either.

A2b-063.name: Lickilicky
A2b-063.text:
Lickilicky’s strange tongue can stretch to many
times the length of its body. No one has figured
out how Lickilicky’s tongue can stretch so far.

A2b-064.name: Bidoof
A2b-064.text:
With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is
more agile and active than it appears.

A2b-065.name: Bibarel ex

attack.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

A2b-065.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A2b-066.name: Buneary
A2b-066.text:
If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, something
is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the
Pokémon is in need of care.

A2b-067.name: Lopunny
A2b-067.text:
Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings.
If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds
with superdestructive kicks.

A2b-068.name: Cyclizar

attack.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Overacceleration attack does +20 damage.

A2b-068.text:
Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to
ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of
this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

A3-004.text:
It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in
any direction—to and fro and sideways.

A3-006.name: Karrablast
A3-006.text:
Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways.
The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

A3-007.name: Phantump
A3-007.text:
After a lost child perished in the forest,
their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing
the spirit’s rebirth as this Pokémon.

A3-008.name: Trevenant
A3-008.text:
People fear it due to a belief that it devours any
who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the
Pokémon it shares its woods with, it’s kind.

A3-009.name: Rowlet
A3-009.text:
It sends its feathers, which are as sharp
as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong,
so its kicks are also formidable.

A3-014.name: Fomantis
A3-014.text:
Fomantis hates having its naps interrupted.
It fires off beams using energy it gathers by
bathing in the sun.

A3-015.name: Lurantis
A3-015.text:
By masquerading as a bug Pokémon, it lowers the
guard of actual bug Pokémon lured in by a scent of
sweet flowers. Its sickles bring them down.

A3-018.name: Bounsweet
A3-018.text:
Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled-down
fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in
the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

A3-019.name: Steenee
A3-019.text:
Steenee spreads a sweet scent that
makes others feel invigorated. This same
scent is popular for antiperspirants.

A3-020.name: Tsareena
A3-020.text:
This Pokémon is proud and aggressive. However, it is
said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if
someone touches the crown on its calyx.

A3-021.name: Wimpod

ability.effect: During your first turn, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

A3-021.text:
It’s nature’s cleaner—it eats anything and everything,
including garbage and rotten things. The ground near
its nest is always clean.

A3-022.name: Golisopod
A3-022.text:
It will do anything to win, taking advantage
of every opening and finishing opponents
off with the small claws on its front legs.

A3-023.name: Dhelmise ex
A3-023.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-024.name: Tapu Bulu
A3-024.text:
Although it’s called a guardian deity, it’s violent
enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

A3-025.name: Growlithe
A3-025.text:
It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly
stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

A3-028.name: Fletchinder
A3-028.text:
Fletchinder scatters embers in tall grass
where bug Pokémon might be hiding and
then catches them as they come leaping out.

A3-029.name: Talonflame
A3-029.text:
It has top-notch flying capabilities. It flies
around easily, even while carrying prey
that weighs more than 220 lbs.

A3-030.name: Litten
A3-030.text:
If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t
open up to you. Even if you do grow close,
giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

A3-032.name: Torracat
A3-032.text:
Torracat will let its Trainer coddle it once they’ve
grown close, but it’s a powerful, sharp-clawed
Pokémon, so its Trainer gets covered in scratches.

A3-033.name: Incineroar ex
A3-033.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-035.name: Salandit
A3-035.text:
It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow,
rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic
gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

A3-036.name: Salazzle
A3-036.text:
Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with
poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring
movements to turn them into loyal servants.

A3-039.name: Alolan Sandslash
A3-039.text:
It uses large, hooked claws to cut a path through
deep snow as it runs. On snowy mountains, this
Sandslash is faster than any other Pokémon.

A3-042.name: Shellder
A3-042.text:
It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond.
Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

A3-043.name: Cloyster
A3-043.text:
Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents
grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

A3-046.name: Popplio
A3-046.text:
The balloons it inflates with its nose grow
larger and larger as it practices day by day.

A3-049.name: Crabominable ex
A3-049.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-052.name: Dewpider
A3-052.text:
It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body
and then covers its head with it. Meeting another
Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

A3-053.name: Araquanid
A3-053.text:
It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the
bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

A3-057.name: Pikachu
A3-057.text:
When it is angered, it immediately discharges the
energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

A3-058.name: Alolan Raichu ex
A3-058.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-059.name: Alolan Geodude
A3-059.text:
If you mistake it for a rock and step on it,
it will headbutt you in anger. In addition to
the pain, it will also zap you with a shock.

A3-060.name: Alolan Graveler
A3-060.text:
When two Graveler fight each other, it fills the
surroundings with flashes of light and sound.
People call it the “fireworks of the earth.”

A3-061.name: Alolan Golem
A3-061.text:
It’s grumpy and stubborn. If you upset it,
it discharges electricity from the surface of
its body and growls with a voice like thunder.

A3-062.name: Helioptile
A3-062.text:
When spread, the frills on its head act like solar
panels, generating the power behind this
Pokémon’s electric moves.

A3-066.name: Oricorio

ability.effect: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon ex.

A3-066.text:
This form of Oricorio has sipped yellow nectar.
It uses nimble steps to approach opponents,
then knocks them out with electric punches.

A3-068.name: Tapu Koko
A3-068.text:
Although it’s called a guardian deity, if a
person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood,
it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

A3-069.name: Mr. Mime
A3-069.text:
The broadness of its hands may be no
coincidence—many scientists believe its palms
became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

A3-072.name: Grumpig
A3-072.text:
It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes.
Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

A3-076.name: Oricorio
A3-076.text:
This form of Oricorio has sipped pink nectar.
It elevates its mind with the gentle steps of its
dance, then unleashes its psychic energy.

A3-078.name: Cutiefly
A3-078.text:
Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare.
In fields of flowers, it gets into skirmishes
with Butterfree over food.

A3-079.name: Ribombee
A3-079.text:
It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar.
The puffs’ effects depend on the type of
ingredients and how much of each one is used.

A3-080.name: Comfey

ability.effect: Each of your Pokémon that has any Energy attached recovers from all Special Conditions and can’t be affected by any Special Conditions.

A3-080.text:
Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates
itself with them. For some reason, flowers won’t
wither once they’re attached to a Comfey.

A3-081.name: Sandygast
A3-081.text:
If it loses its shovel, it will stick something
else—like a branch—in its head to make
do until it finds another shovel.

A3-082.name: Palossand
A3-082.text:
The terrifying Palossand drags smaller Pokémon
into its sandy body. Once its victims are trapped,
it drains them of their vitality whenever it pleases.

A3-086.name: Cosmoem
A3-086.text:
The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it
the “cocoon of the stars” and built an altar to worship it.

A3-090.name: Makuhita
A3-090.text:
It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is
a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.

A3-092.name: Solrock
A3-092.text:
When it rotates itself, it gives off light
similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.

A3-097.name: Crabrawler
A3-097.text:
This Pokémon punches trees and eats
the berries that drop down, training itself
and getting food at the same time.

A3-099.name: Rockruff
A3-099.text:
This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young.
Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures,
but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

A3-100.name: Lycanroc
A3-100.text:
Lycanroc attacks its prey with its
sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys
the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

A3-102.name: Mudbray
A3-102.text:
This Pokémon covers itself in mud that it
has regurgitated. The mud won’t dry out even
if it’s exposed to the sun for a long time.

A3-103.name: Mudsdale
A3-103.text:
This Pokémon has been treasured not just
for its physical labor but also because it produces
high-quality mud used for making pottery.

A3-108.name: Alolan Meowth
A3-108.text:
It’s accustomed to luxury because it
used to live with Alolan royalty. As a
result, it’s very picky about food.

A3-109.name: Alolan Persian

ability.effect: This Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

A3-109.text:
The round face of Alolan Persian is considered
to be a symbol of prosperity in the Alola region,
so these Pokémon are very well cared for.

A3-113.name: Trubbish
A3-113.text:
Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you
leave trash lying around, you could even find
one of these Pokémon living in your room.

A3-117.name: Alolan Diglett
A3-117.text:
The metal-rich geology of this Pokémon’s habitat
caused it to develop steel whiskers on its head.

A3-118.name: Alolan Dugtrio
A3-118.text:
Their beautiful, metallic whiskers create a sort of
protective helmet on their heads, and they also
function as highly precise sensors.

A3-119.name: Excadrill
A3-119.text:
It’s not uncommon for tunnels that appear to
have formed naturally to actually be a result
of Excadrill’s rampant digging.

A3-120.name: Escavalier
A3-120.text:
Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet,
they defend themselves and attack with two lances.

A3-121.name: Klefki
A3-121.text:
Once it absorbs a key’s metal ions, it discards the
key without a second thought. However, it will
hang on to keys it favors for decades.

A3-122.name: Solgaleo ex

ability.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.

A3-122.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-123.name: Magearna
A3-123.text:
It synchronizes its consciousness with others
to understand their feelings. This faculty makes
it useful for taking care of people.

A3-124.name: Drampa
A3-124.text:
The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles
in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play
with the children living in the towns below.

A3-131.name: Fletchling
A3-131.text:
This Pokémon is normally calm, but once it enters battle,
its hormonal balance changes and it becomes aggressive.

A3-132.name: Hawlucha
A3-132.text:
Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly
leaping around using its wings—are polished in
the forest where it was born and raised.

A3-134.name: Trumbeak
A3-134.text:
It can bend the tip of its beak to produce
over a hundred different cries at will.

A3-135.name: Toucannon
A3-135.text:
They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate.
The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.

A3-136.name: Yungoos
A3-136.text:
Its stomach fills most of its torso. It wanders the
same path every day, searching for fresh food.

A3-137.name: Gumshoos
A3-137.text:
Once it finds signs of prey, it will patiently stake
out the location, waiting until the sun goes down.

A3-141.name: Komala

ability.effect: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, whenever you attach an Energy from your Energy Zone to it, it is now Asleep.

A3-141.text:
Komala spends its entire life sleeping.
It feeds on leaves that contain a potent
poison only Komala can break down.

A3-142.rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

A3-144.rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

A3-145.rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare.

A3-169.text:
If it loses its shovel, it will stick something

do until it finds another shovel.

A3-176.text:
The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles

A3-209.name: Lillie
A3-209.rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

A3-210.name: Bulbasaur
A3-210.text:
There is a plant seed on its back right from the
day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly
grows larger.

A3-211.name: Ivysaur
A3-211.text:
When the bulb on its back grows large, it
appears to lose the ability to stand on its
hind legs.

A3-212.name: Venusaur
A3-212.text:
Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar
energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

A3-218.name: Staryu
A3-218.text:
If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you’ll
be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a
steady rhythm.

A3-219.name: Starmie
A3-219.text:
This Pokémon has an organ known as its core.
The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is
unleashing its potent psychic powers.

A3-223.name: Machop
A3-223.text:
Its whole body is composed of muscles.
Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can
hurl 100 grown-ups.

A3-224.name: Machoke
A3-224.text:
Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a
power-save belt to be able to regulate
its motions.

A3-225.name: Machamp
A3-225.text:
It quickly swings its four arms to rock its
opponents with ceaseless punches and chops
from all angles.

A3-228.name: Jigglypuff
A3-228.text:
When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously
soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

A3-229.name: Wigglytuff

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Pokémon.

A3-229.text:
It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it
angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a
body slam.

A3-230.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-233.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-235.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-237.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may move all Energy from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to your Active Pokémon.

A3-238.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-239.name: Solgaleo ex

ability.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.

A3-239.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-001.name: Exeggcute
A3-001.text:
Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs,
it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates
with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

A3-002.name: Alolan Exeggutor
A3-002.text:
Blazing sunlight has brought out the true
form and powers of this Pokémon.

A3-003.name: Surskit
A3-003.text:
They usually live on ponds, but after an evening
shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.

A3-005.name: Maractus
A3-005.text:
With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles
of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling
bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

A3-010.name: Rowlet
A3-010.text:
It sends its feathers, which are as sharp
as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong,
so its kicks are also formidable.

A3-011.name: Dartrix
A3-011.text:
This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you
don’t groom it diligently, it may stop listening to you.

A3-012.name: Decidueye ex
A3-012.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-013.name: Grubbin
A3-013.text:
Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting
caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.

A3-016.name: Morelull
A3-016.text:
Pokémon living in the forest eat the
delicious caps on Morelull’s head.
The caps regrow overnight.

A3-017.name: Shiinotic
A3-017.text:
Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to
sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing,
it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

A3-026.name: Arcanine
A3-026.text:
An ancient picture scroll shows that people
were captivated by its movement as it ran
through prairies.

A3-027.name: Alolan Marowak
A3-027.text:
This Pokémon sets the bone it holds
on fire and dances through the night
as a way to mourn its fallen allies.

A3-031.name: Litten
A3-031.text:
If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t
open up to you. Even if you do grow close,
giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

A3-034.name: Oricorio
A3-034.text:
This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up
blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.

A3-037.name: Turtonator
A3-037.text:
Explosive substances coat the shell on
its back. Enemies that dare attack it will
be blown away by an immense detonation.

A3-038.name: Alolan Sandshrew
A3-038.text:
Life on mountains covered with deep snow has granted
this Pokémon a body of ice that’s as hard as steel.

A3-040.name: Alolan Vulpix
A3-040.text:
After long years in the ever-snowcapped mountains
of Alola, this Vulpix has gained power over ice.

A3-041.name: Alolan Ninetales
A3-041.text:
A deity resides in the snowy mountains
where this Pokémon lives. In ancient times,
it was worshiped as that deity’s incarnation.

A3-044.name: Lapras
A3-044.text:
A smart and kindhearted Pokémon,
it glides across the surface of the sea while
its beautiful song echoes around it.

A3-045.name: Popplio
A3-045.text:
The balloons it inflates with its nose grow
larger and larger as it practices day by day.

A3-047.name: Brionne
A3-047.text:
It gets excited when it sees a dance it
doesn’t know. This hard worker practices
diligently until it can learn that dance.

A3-048.name: Primarina

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 30 damage from each of your Pokémon.

A3-048.text:
To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes
down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

A3-050.name: Wishiwashi
A3-050.text:
Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering
up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.

A3-051.name: Wishiwashi ex
A3-051.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-054.name: Pyukumuku

ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon, do 50 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

A3-054.text:
It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a
foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means
to punch them.

A3-055.name: Bruxish
A3-055.text:
It grinds its teeth with great force to stimulate
its brain. It fires the psychic energy created by
this process from the protuberance on its head.

A3-056.name: Tapu Fini
A3-056.text:
This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates
water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog,
it came to be both feared and revered.

A3-063.name: Heliolisk
A3-063.text:
One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill
outspread is all it would take to produce enough
electricity to power a city.

A3-064.name: Charjabug
A3-064.text:
While its durable shell protects it from attacks,
Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of
electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

A3-065.name: Vikavolt
A3-065.text:
It builds up electricity in its abdomen,
focuses it through its jaws, and then fires
the electricity off in concentrated beams.

A3-067.name: Togedemaru
A3-067.text:
With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon
takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon.
It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

A3-070.name: Sableye
A3-070.text:
It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its
sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

A3-071.name: Spoink
A3-071.text:
Spoink will die if it stops bouncing. The pearl
on its head amplifies its psychic powers.

A3-073.name: Lunatone
A3-073.text:
The phase of the moon apparently has some effect
on its power. It’s active on the night of a full moon.

A3-074.name: Shuppet
A3-074.text:
It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice.
Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.

A3-075.name: Banette
A3-075.text:
This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll
that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

A3-077.name: Oricorio
A3-077.text:
This form of Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. It uses
ethereal dance steps to call forth the spirits of the dead.

A3-083.name: Mimikyu
A3-083.text:
There was a scientist who peeked under
Mimikyu’s old rag in the name of research.
The scientist died of a mysterious disease.

A3-084.name: Tapu Lele
A3-084.text:
It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon
by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales.
This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

A3-085.name: Cosmog
A3-085.text:
Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown
away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.

A3-087.name: Lunala ex

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may move all Energy from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to your Active Pokémon.

A3-087.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-088.name: Necrozma
A3-088.text:
It looks somehow pained as it rages around
in search of light, which serves as its energy.
It’s apparently from another world.

A3-089.name: Cubone
A3-089.text:
When the memory of its departed mother brings
it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the
skull it wears on its head.

A3-091.name: Hariyama
A3-091.text:
It loves challenging others to tests of strength.
It has the power to stop a train with a slap.

A3-093.name: Drilbur
A3-093.text:
It brings its claws together and whirls around
at high speed before rushing toward its prey.

A3-094.name: Timburr
A3-094.text:
It loves helping out with construction projects.
It loves it so much that if rain causes work to
halt, it swings its log around and throws a tantrum.

A3-095.name: Gurdurr
A3-095.text:
It shows off its muscles to Machoke and
other Gurdurr. If it fails to measure up to the
other Pokémon, it lies low for a little while.

A3-096.name: Conkeldurr

ability.effect: If this Pokémon would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokémon is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.

A3-096.text:
Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more
durable than normal concrete, even when the
compositions of the two materials are the same.

A3-098.name: Rockruff
A3-098.text:
This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young.
Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures,
but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

A3-101.name: Lycanroc
A3-101.text:
This Pokémon uses its rocky mane to slash
any who approach. It will even disobey its
Trainer if it dislikes the orders it was given.

A3-104.name: Passimian ex

ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon, move all Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

A3-104.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-105.name: Minior
A3-105.text:
Places where Minior fall from the night
sky are few and far between, with Alola
being one of the precious few.

A3-106.name: Alolan Rattata
A3-106.text:
It shows no interest in anything that
isn’t fresh. If you take it shopping with
you, it will help you pick out ingredients.

A3-107.name: Alolan Raticate
A3-107.text:
It has an incredibly greedy personality. Its nest
is filled with so much food gathered by Rattata
at its direction, it can’t possibly eat it all.

A3-110.name: Alolan Grimer
A3-110.text:
There are a hundred or so of them living in
Alola’s waste-disposal site. They’re all hard
workers who eat a lot of trash.

A3-111.name: Alolan Muk ex
A3-111.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-112.name: Absol
A3-112.text:
Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and
mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely
sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

A3-114.name: Garbodor
A3-114.text:
This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison
inside its body. The main component of the
poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

A3-115.name: Mareanie
A3-115.text:
This Pokémon wanders the seaside looking for
food. It often gets electric shocks from broken
Pincurchin spines that it tries to eat.

A3-116.name: Toxapex
A3-116.text:
This Pokémon lives within a dome made by its
own legs. Toxapex monitors its surroundings by
sensing the flow of the tide through its spikes.

A3-125.name: Jangmo-o
A3-125.text:
They learn to fight by smashing their head scales together.
The dueling strengthens both their skills and their spirits.

A3-126.name: Hakamo-o
A3-126.text:
The scaleless, scarred parts of its
body are signs of its strength. It shows
them off to defeated opponents.

A3-127.name: Kommo-o
A3-127.text:
It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents.
This Pokémon will battle only those who stand
steadfast in the face of this display.

A3-128.name: Tauros
A3-128.text:
When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails,
it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to
charge with astounding speed.

A3-129.name: Skitty
A3-129.text:
It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things,
and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.

A3-130.name: Delcatty
A3-130.text:
It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a
comfortable place in which to groom itself.

A3-133.name: Pikipek
A3-133.text:
It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some
idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

A3-138.name: Stufful
A3-138.text:
Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out
to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

A3-139.name: Bewear
A3-139.text:
Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show
its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is
dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

A3-140.name: Oranguru
A3-140.text:
People used to mistake Oranguru for a human
when they saw it issue command after command
to the other Pokémon of the forest.

A3-143.name: Fishing Net
A3-143.rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

A3-148.rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

A3-149.rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

A3-150.rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

A3-151.rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

A3-156.name: Alolan Exeggutor
A3-156.text:
Blazing sunlight has brought out the true
form and powers of this Pokémon.

A3-157.name: Morelull
A3-157.text:
Pokémon living in the forest eat the
delicious caps on Morelull’s head.
The caps regrow overnight.

A3-160.name: Alolan Marowak
A3-160.text:
This Pokémon sets the bone it holds
on fire and dances through the night
as a way to mourn its fallen allies.

A3-161.name: Turtonator
A3-161.text:
Explosive substances coat the shell on
its back. Enemies that dare attack it will
be blown away by an immense detonation.

A3-162.name: Alolan Vulpix
A3-162.text:
After long years in the ever-snowcapped mountains
of Alola, this Vulpix has gained power over ice.

A3-163.name: Pyukumuku

ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon, do 50 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

A3-163.text:
It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a
foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means
to punch them.

A3-164.name: Tapu Fini
A3-164.text:
This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates
water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog,
it came to be both feared and revered.

A3-170.name: Tapu Lele
A3-170.text:
It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon
by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales.
This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

A3-171.name: Cosmog
A3-171.text:
Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown
away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.

A3-174.name: Minior
A3-174.text:
Places where Minior fall from the night
sky are few and far between, with Alola
being one of the precious few.

A3-177.name: Pikipek
A3-177.text:
It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some
idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

A3-178.name: Bewear
A3-178.text:
Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show
its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is
dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

A3-213.name: Exeggcute
A3-213.text:
Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs,
it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates
with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

A3-214.name: Exeggutor
A3-214.text:
Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking
different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be
very interested in one another.

A3-215.name: Squirtle
A3-215.text:
When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it
squirts out water with vigorous force.

A3-216.name: Wartortle
A3-216.text:
It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its
shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

A3-217.name: Blastoise
A3-217.text:
It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause
fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

A3-220.name: Gastly
A3-220.text:
It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body,
slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it
through the skin.

A3-221.name: Haunter
A3-221.text:
It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders
with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless
shuddering.

A3-222.name: Gengar
A3-222.text:
To steal the life of its target, it slips into
the prey’s shadow and silently waits for
an opportunity.

A3-226.name: Cubone
A3-226.text:
When the memory of its departed mother brings
it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the
skull it wears on its head.

A3-227.name: Marowak
A3-227.text:
This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a
sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents
bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

A3-231.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-232.name: Blastoise ex
A3-232.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

ability.effect: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can’t use any Supporter cards from their hand.

A3-234.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3-236.name: Marowak ex
A3-236.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3a-001.name: Petilil
A3a-001.text:
The leaves on its head grow right back even if
they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those
who eat them.

A3a-002.name: Lilligant
A3a-002.text:
The fragrance of the garland on its head has
a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very
difficult.

A3a-003.name: Rowlet
A3a-003.text:
It sends its feathers, which are as sharp
as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong,
so its kicks are also formidable.

A3a-004.name: Dartrix
A3a-004.text:
This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you
don’t groom it diligently, it may stop listening to you.

A3a-005.name: Decidueye
A3a-005.text:
It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at
opponents. When it simply can’t afford to miss,
it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.

A3a-006.name: Buzzwole ex
A3a-006.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3a-007.name: Pheromosa
A3a-007.text:
A life-form that lives in another world, its body
is thin and supple, but it also possesses
great power.

A3a-008.name: Kartana
A3a-008.text:
This Ultra Beast’s body, which is as thin
as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

A3a-009.name: Blacephalon
A3a-009.text:
It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the
explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

A3a-010.name: Mantine
A3a-010.text:
If it builds up enough speed swimming, it
can jump out above the waves and glide
for over 300 feet.

A3a-011.name: Carvanha
A3a-011.text:
It won’t attack while it’s alone—not even if it
spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to
join it, and then the Pokémon attack as a group.

A3a-012.name: Sharpedo
A3a-012.text:
As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo
will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling
toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

A3a-013.name: Shinx
A3a-013.text:
The extension and contraction of its muscles
generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

A3a-014.name: Luxio
A3a-014.text:
Strong electricity courses through the tips of
its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting
in foes.

A3a-015.name: Luxray

ability.effect: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, attacks used by your opponent’s Active Pokémon do −20 damage.

A3a-015.text:
It can see clearly through walls to track down its
prey and seek its lost young.

A3a-016.name: Blitzle
A3a-016.text:
When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear.
It can catch lightning with its mane and store
the electricity.

A3a-017.name: Zebstrika
A3a-017.text:
When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it
shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

A3a-018.name: Emolga
A3a-018.text:
As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles
with electricity. This Pokémon is cute, but it can
cause a lot of trouble.

A3a-019.name: Tapu Koko ex
A3a-019.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3a-020.name: Xurkitree
A3a-020.text:
Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently
a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

A3a-021.name: Zeraora

ability.effect: At the end of your first turn, take a Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

A3a-021.text:
It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents
apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack,
they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

A3a-022.name: Clefairy
A3a-022.text:
It is said that happiness will come to those who
see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a
full moon.

A3a-023.name: Clefable
A3a-023.text:
A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will
run and hide the moment it senses people.

A3a-024.name: Phantump
A3a-024.text:
With a voice like a human child’s, it cries out to
lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost
among the trees.

A3a-025.name: Trevenant
A3a-025.text:
People fear it due to a belief that it devours any
who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the
Pokémon it shares its woods with, it’s kind.

A3a-026.name: Morelull
A3a-026.text:
It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone
seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

A3a-027.name: Shiinotic

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may put a random Pokémon from your deck into your hand.

A3a-027.text:
Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to
sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing,
it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

A3a-028.name: Meditite
A3a-028.text:
It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens
its inner strength through meditation.

A3a-029.name: Medicham
A3a-029.text:
Through yoga training, it gained the psychic
power to predict its foe’s next move.

A3a-030.name: Baltoy
A3a-030.text:
It moves while spinning around on its single foot.
Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on
their heads.

A3a-031.name: Claydol

ability.effect: Pokémon (both yours and your opponent’s) can’t be healed.

A3a-031.text:
This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient
clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.

A3a-032.name: Rockruff
A3a-032.text:
This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young.
Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures,
but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

A3a-033.name: Lycanroc ex
A3a-033.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3a-034.name: Passimian
A3a-034.text:
This Pokémon battles by throwing hard berries.
It won’t obey a Trainer who throws Poké Balls
without skill.

A3a-035.name: Sandygast
A3a-035.text:
If it loses its shovel, it will stick something
else—like a branch—in its head to make
do until it finds another shovel.

A3a-036.name: Palossand
A3a-036.text:
The terrifying Palossand drags smaller Pokémon
into its sandy body. Once its victims are trapped,
it drains them of their vitality whenever it pleases.

A3a-037.name: Alolan Meowth
A3a-037.text:
It’s accustomed to luxury because it
used to live with Alolan royalty. As a
result, it’s very picky about food.

A3a-038.name: Alolan Persian
A3a-038.text:
The round face of Alolan Persian is considered
to be a symbol of prosperity in the Alola region,
so these Pokémon are very well cared for.

A3a-039.name: Sandile
A3a-039.text:
It submerges itself in sand and moves as if
swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies
from finding it and maintains its temperature.

A3a-040.name: Krokorok
A3a-040.text:
Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see
even in the dead of night. They live in groups of
a few individuals.

A3a-041.name: Krookodile
A3a-041.text:
After clamping down with its powerful jaws, it
twists its body around to rip its prey in half.

A3a-042.name: Nihilego

ability.effect: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon takes +10 damage from being Poisoned.

A3a-042.text:
A life-form from another world, it was dubbed
a UB and is thought to produce a
strong neurotoxin.

A3a-043.name: Guzzlord ex
A3a-043.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3a-044.name: Poipole
A3a-044.text:
This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be
chosen as a first partner in its own world.

A3a-045.name: Naganadel
A3a-045.text:
It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid
inside its body. It is one of the organisms known
as UBs.

A3a-046.name: Alolan Diglett
A3a-046.text:
The metal-rich geology of this Pokémon’s habitat
caused it to develop steel whiskers on its head.

A3a-047.name: Alolan Dugtrio ex
A3a-047.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3a-048.name: Aron
A3a-048.text:
It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks—
to build up the steel armor that protects its body.

A3a-049.name: Lairon
A3a-049.text:
It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory
by bashing one another with their steel bodies.

A3a-050.name: Aggron
A3a-050.text:
Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate
thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by
ramming into them horn first.

A3a-051.name: Ferroseed
A3a-051.text:
It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging
to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

A3a-052.name: Ferrothorn

ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

A3a-052.text:
This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks,
and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb
the nutrients it finds within the stone.

A3a-053.name: Stakataka
A3a-053.text:
It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one
appears to be made up of many life-forms
stacked one on top of each other.

A3a-054.name: Lillipup
A3a-054.text:
This Pokémon is courageous but also cautious.
It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect
information about its surroundings.

A3a-055.name: Herdier
A3a-055.text:
Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokémon.
So much so that there’s a theory that Herdier was
the first Pokémon to partner with people.

A3a-056.name: Stoutland

ability.effect: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, attacks used by your opponent’s Active Pokémon cost 1 more.

A3a-056.text:
These Pokémon seem to enjoy living with humans.
Even a Stoutland caught in the wild will warm up
to people in about three days.

A3a-057.name: Stufful
A3a-057.text:
Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out
to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

A3a-058.name: Bewear
A3a-058.text:
Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show
its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is
dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

A3a-059.name: Oranguru
A3a-059.text:
It normally spends its time meditating in the
treetops. It throws Poké Balls and gives other
Pokémon orders as it pleases.

A3a-060.name: Type: Null
A3a-060.text:
A Pokémon weapon developed for a specific
mission, it went berserk during an experiment,
so it was cryogenically frozen.

A3a-061.name: Silvally
A3a-061.text:
This is its form once it has awakened and
evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is
greatly increased.

A3a-062.name: Celesteela

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may switch your Active Ultra Beast with 1 of your Benched Ultra Beasts.

A3a-062.text:
One of the dangerous UBs, high energy readings
can be detected coming from both of its
huge arms.

A3a-063.rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

A3a-064.name: Repel
A3a-064.rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

A3a-067.rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

A3a-068.name: Looker
A3a-068.rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

A3a-069.name: Lusamine
A3a-069.rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

A3a-070.name: Rowlet
A3a-070.text:
It sends its feathers, which are as sharp
as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong,
so its kicks are also formidable.

A3a-071.name: Pheromosa
A3a-071.text:
A life-form that lives in another world, its body
is thin and supple, but it also possesses
great power.

A3a-072.text:
It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the
explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

A3a-073.text:
It’s accustomed to luxury because it
used to live with Alolan royalty. As a
result, it’s very picky about food.

A3a-074.name: Silvally

This is its form once it has awakened and
evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is
greatly increased.

can be detected coming from both of its
huge arms.

It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly

A3a-090.name: Arcanine
A3a-090.text:
An ancient picture scroll shows that people
were captivated by its movement as it ran
through prairies.

A3a-091.name: Froakie
A3a-091.text:
It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back.
The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise
take when attacked.

A3a-092.name: Frogadier
A3a-092.text:
It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise
control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

A3a-093.name: Greninja

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may do 20 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon.

A3a-093.text:
It creates throwing stars out of compressed water.
When it spins them and throws them at high speed,
these stars can split metal in two.

A3a-094.name: Jynx
A3a-094.text:
Its strange cries sound like human language.
There are some musicians who compose songs
for Jynx to sing.

A3a-095.name: Pidgey
A3a-095.text:
A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps
its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

A3a-096.name: Pidgeotto
A3a-096.text:
The claws on its feet are well developed.
It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute
to its nest over 60 miles away.

A3a-097.name: Pidgeot

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may switch out your opponent’s Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

A3a-097.text:
When hunting, it skims the surface of water
at high speed to pick off unwary prey such
as Magikarp.

A3a-098.name: Aerodactyl
A3a-098.text:
This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times.
Apparently even modern technology is incapable
of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

A3a-103.text:
A life-form from another world, it was dubbed
a UB and is thought to produce a
strong neurotoxin.

A3b-001.name: Tropius
A3b-001.text:
It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit
around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows
twice a year.

A3b-002.name: Leafeon
A3b-002.text:
When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of
sunshine, you’ll know it is using photosynthesis
to produce clean air.

A3b-003.name: Bounsweet
A3b-003.text:
Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled-down
fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in
the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

A3b-004.name: Steenee
A3b-004.text:
Steenee spreads a sweet scent that
makes others feel invigorated. This same
scent is popular for antiperspirants.

A3b-005.name: Tsareena
A3b-005.text:
This Pokémon is proud and aggressive. However, it is
said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if
someone touches the crown on its calyx.

A3b-006.name: Applin
A3b-006.text:
It grows by eating the flesh of an apple.
Applin uses its own body fluid to strengthen
the apple’s skin and prevent it from rotting.

A3b-007.name: Appletun
A3b-007.text:
It feeds mainly on sweet apples. It will also eat
small bug Pokémon that are attracted by its
sweet nectar.

A3b-008.name: Flareon
A3b-008.text:
Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and
exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees
Fahrenheit.

A3b-009.name: Flareon ex

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may attach a Energy from your discard pile to this Pokémon. If you do, do 20 damage to this Pokémon.

A3b-009.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3b-010.name: Torkoal
A3b-010.text:
It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows
out black soot if it is endangered.

A3b-011.name: Litten
A3b-011.text:
If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t
open up to you. Even if you do grow close,
giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

A3b-012.name: Torracat
A3b-012.text:
Torracat will let its Trainer coddle it once they’ve
grown close, but it’s a powerful, sharp-clawed
Pokémon, so its Trainer gets covered in scratches.

A3b-013.name: Incineroar
A3b-013.text:
Although it’s rough mannered and egotistical, it
finds beating down unworthy opponents boring.
It gets motivated for stronger opponents.

A3b-014.name: Salandit
A3b-014.text:
It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow,
rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic
gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

A3b-015.name: Salazzle
A3b-015.text:
Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with
poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring
movements to turn them into loyal servants.

A3b-016.name: Vaporeon
A3b-016.text:
It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with
a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

A3b-017.name: Glaceon
A3b-017.text:
It can control its body temperature at will.
This enables it to freeze the moisture in the
atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.

A3b-018.name: Vanillite
A3b-018.text:
Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself
comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to
cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.

A3b-019.name: Vanillish
A3b-019.text:
By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body.
This Pokémon can be hard to find on days with
warm, sunny weather.

A3b-020.name: Vanilluxe
A3b-020.text:
When its anger reaches a breaking point, this
Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes
every creature around it, be they friend or foe.

A3b-021.name: Alomomola
A3b-021.text:
It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its
fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

A3b-022.name: Popplio
A3b-022.text:
The balloons it inflates with its nose grow
larger and larger as it practices day by day.

A3b-023.name: Brionne
A3b-023.text:
It gets excited when it sees a dance it
doesn’t know. This hard worker practices
diligently until it can learn that dance.

A3b-024.name: Primarina ex
A3b-024.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3b-025.name: Jolteon
A3b-025.text:
It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted
by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

A3b-026.name: Joltik
A3b-026.text:
Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon.
It’s soaking up static electricity because it can’t
produce a charge on its own.

A3b-027.name: Galvantula
A3b-027.text:
It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its
means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could
be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.

A3b-028.name: Espeon
A3b-028.text:
The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is
predicting its opponent’s next move.

A3b-029.name: Woobat
A3b-029.text:
While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots
of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it’s
evidence that Woobat live there.

A3b-030.name: Swoobat
A3b-030.text:
Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out.
Afterward, it won’t be able to fly for a
little while.

A3b-031.name: Swirlix
A3b-031.text:
It eats its own weight in sugar every day.
If it doesn’t get enough sugar, it becomes
incredibly grumpy.

A3b-032.name: Slurpuff
A3b-032.text:
By taking in a person’s scent, it can sniff out their
mental and physical condition. It’s hoped that
this skill will have many medical applications.

A3b-033.name: Sylveon
A3b-033.text:
This Pokémon uses its ribbonlike feelers to send
a soothing aura into its opponents, erasing
their hostility.

A3b-034.name: Sylveon ex

ability.effect: Once during your turn, when you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may draw 2 cards.

A3b-034.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3b-035.name: Mimikyu
A3b-035.text:
This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by
sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides
itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

A3b-036.name: Milcery
A3b-036.text:
This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling
particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

A3b-037.name: Alcremie
A3b-037.text:
When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them
to berries it’s decorated with cream.

A3b-038.name: Barboach
A3b-038.text:
Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in
muddy waters, it can detect its prey’s location.

A3b-039.name: Whiscash
A3b-039.text:
It is extremely protective of its territory. If any
foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.

A3b-040.name: Mienfoo
A3b-040.text:
In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop
with its arms more than 100 times.

A3b-041.name: Mienshao
A3b-041.text:
When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging
opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the
fur on its arms.

A3b-042.name: Carbink
A3b-042.text:
When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all
out by firing high-energy beams from the gems
embedded in its body.

A3b-043.name: Umbreon
A3b-043.text:
When exposed to the moon’s aura, the rings on its
body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.

A3b-044.name: Sableye
A3b-044.text:
Materials from gems it has eaten float to the
surface of its body and can form an infinite
number of patterns among individuals.

A3b-045.name: Purrloin
A3b-045.text:
Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable
behavior come away with stinging scratches from
its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

A3b-046.name: Liepard
A3b-046.text:
Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant
figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

A3b-047.name: Mawile
A3b-047.text:
It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into
complacency, then bites with its huge,
relentless jaws.

A3b-048.name: Togedemaru
A3b-048.text:
With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon
takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon.
It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

A3b-049.name: Meltan
A3b-049.text:
It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid
metal within its body is how it generates energy.

A3b-050.name: Melmetal
A3b-050.text:
At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and
fall apart. The small shards left behind will
eventually be reborn as Meltan.

A3b-051.name: Dratini
A3b-051.text:
It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger.
During this process, it is protected by a rapid
waterfall.

A3b-052.name: Dragonair
A3b-052.text:
They say that if it emits an aura from its whole
body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

A3b-053.name: Dragonite ex
A3b-053.rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

A3b-054.name: Drampa
A3b-054.text:
The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles
in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play
with the children living in the towns below.

A3b-055.name: Eevee
A3b-055.text:
Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to
adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

A3b-058.name: Aipom
A3b-058.text:
As it did more and more with its tail, its hands
became clumsy. It makes its nest high in
the treetops.

A3b-059.name: Ambipom

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may put a random Pokémon Tool card from your deck into your hand.

A3b-059.text:
It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both
of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze,
that’s proof it really likes you.

A3b-060.name: Chatot
A3b-060.text:
It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them
into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t
attack it.

A3b-061.name: Audino
A3b-061.text:
This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers,
Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.

A3b-062.name: Minccino
A3b-062.text:
The way it brushes away grime with its tail
can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on
spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.

A3b-063.name: Cinccino
A3b-063.text:
Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads
over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust.
Cinccino won’t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

A3b-064.name: Skwovet
A3b-064.text:
It stores berries in its cheeks. When there are no
berries to be found, Skwovet will stuff pebbles
into its cheeks to stave off its cravings.

A3b-065.name: Greedent
A3b-065.text:
This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping
them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.

A3b-093.name: Pinsir
A3b-093.text:
These Pokémon judge one another based on
pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make
for more popularity with the opposite gender.

A3b-094.name: Lapras
A3b-094.text:
A smart and kindhearted Pokémon,
it glides across the surface of the sea while
its beautiful song echoes around it.

A3b-095.name: Voltorb
A3b-095.text:
It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden
jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

A3b-096.name: Electrode
A3b-096.text:
The more energy it charges up, the faster
it gets. But this also makes it more likely
to explode.

A3b-097.name: Ralts
A3b-097.text:
The horns on its head provide a strong power
that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

A3b-098.name: Kirlia
A3b-098.text:
It has a psychic power that enables it to distort
the space around it and see into the future.

A3b-099.name: Gardevoir

ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may take a Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to the Pokémon in the Active Spot.

A3b-099.text:
To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic
power to create a small black hole.

A3b-100.name: Ekans
A3b-100.text:
By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger
than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

A3b-101.name: Arbok
A3b-101.text:
The latest research has determined that there
are over 20 possible arrangements of the
patterns on its stomach.

A3b-102.name: Farfetch’d
A3b-102.text:
The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves
as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire
situation, the stalk can also serve as food.
